        },
        "T_tensile_stress": {
            "code_var_name": "T_tensile_stress",
            "description": "The tensile pre-stress load per unit surface area, a positive scalar quantity.\nJUSTIFICATION:\nThe symbol 'T' is explicitly defined as the positive tensile pre-stress load per unit surface area in the wave equation and appears in both the physical equation and the weak form, especially in the jump condition across interfaces.",
